Upstream license for the Microsoft BASIC for 6502 source in this directory
============================================================================

This directory is Clementina's editable fork of https://github.com/mist64/msbasic
(see CLEMENTINA.md for the recorded upstream commit).

Upstream declares its license only as the words "2-clause BSD" in its README. It
ships no standalone LICENSE file and no explicit copyright line, and GitHub
detects no license for the repository. The text reproduced below is the
canonical BSD 2-Clause License, vendored here so that the attribution condition
is satisfied when this fork is redistributed.

Attribution (per the upstream README "Credits" section):
  - Main work by Michael Steil <mist64@mac.com>
  - AIM-65 and SYM-1 by Martin Hoffmann-Vetter
  - plus the additional contributors credited in README.md

IMPORTANT — scope of this license
---------------------------------
The underlying 6502 Microsoft BASIC code is original Microsoft intellectual
property; the source still embeds notices such as "COPYRIGHT 1977 BY MICROSOFT
CO" (see init.s) and "Copyright Microsoft, Mattel 1980" (see kbd_extra.s).
Michael Steil's BSD license applies to the reconstructed, integrated source
tree and his contributions — it is NOT a grant of rights to Microsoft's
original BASIC code, which has never been formally open-licensed by its owner.
Clementina reuses this code under the same community-tolerated terms as the
upstream project. This is acceptable in practice for a non-commercial,
educational homebrew, but is not a clean license grant. See CLEMENTINA.md.

